        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 5:36PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 536 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Westover Hills, or over Danville, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Providence...
Blairs...
Gatewood...
Dry Fork...
Westover Hills...
and Pelham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
